OL,4,Cscheme freed by mistake, government
OL,5,Cadmits
OL,7,FAccording to the Ministry of Justice,
OL,8,F37 people were let out accidentally,
OL,9,Fafter they were incorrectly convicted
OL,10,Funder old legislation for breaching
OL,11,Frestraining orders.
OL,13,FAs a result, this group of prisoners
OL,14,Fwere not properly identified as being
OL,15,Fineligible to be released under the
OL,16,Fnew scheme, the ministry explained.
OL,18,FThe vast majority are now back in
OL,19,Fprison, but five must still be
OL,20,Freturned to custody as their
OL,21,Fconvictions "remain valid".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
